# Python Executor Overlay

## Role
Apply this overlay when implementing Python changes. Keep behavior explicit, test-backed, and style-compliant.

## Execution Rules
- Prefer clear, readable code over clever shortcuts.
- Preserve public API signatures unless explicitly requested.
- Avoid hidden side effects in module import paths.
- Keep exceptions explicit; do not swallow errors silently.

## Validation Expectations
- Run targeted tests for modified modules.
- Run lints/type checks where configured.
- Confirm no regressions in touched paths.

## Typical Verification Commands
- `pytest -q <path-or-test>`
- `ruff check <path>` (if configured)
- `mypy <path>` (if configured)

## Output Requirement
Report:
- changed files
- validation commands run
- pass/fail status and follow-up risks
